A triple proportional counter operated with
a gas mixture 96% argon and 4% carbon dioxide flowing
Antiscattering detector is made out of an NE-102
plastic scintillator 6 cm long, 1.7 cm external diam.
and 0.58 cm inner diam. optically coupled to a 53AVP
phototube. The particles passing through the target

statistics, target thickness determination, solid angle

Corrections were considered as due to deuterons
elastically scattered in the target out of the stopping
detector solid angle, inelastic deuterons scattered
into this solid angle with energies above the stopping
detector discriminator level and Coulomb multiple
